WEBVTT

1
00:00:04.265 --> 00:00:06.309
<i>Previously on
"The Hunting Party"...</i>

2
00:00:06.310 --> 00:00:07.832
It's called the Pit.

3
00:00:07.833 --> 00:00:09.095
It's home to the most dangerous
and violent criminals

4
00:00:09.096 --> 00:00:10.574
in history.
all of whom the world believes

5
00:00:10.575 --> 00:00:11.793
are dead.

6
00:00:11.794 --> 00:00:14.187
Or at least it was
until the blast hit.

7
00:00:15.754 --> 00:00:17.581
Are you gonna
ask me out or what?

8
00:00:17.582 --> 00:00:19.453
No.

9
00:00:19.454 --> 00:00:22.195
Maybe.

10
00:00:22.196 --> 00:00:24.893
Your father is the
only one who can tell me

11
00:00:24.894 --> 00:00:27.069
<i>who my biological mother is.</i>

12
00:00:27.070 --> 00:00:28.201
<i>Can I speak with him?</i>

13
00:00:28.202 --> 00:00:29.680
<i>You know you can't.</i>

14
00:00:29.681 --> 00:00:31.030
<i>It's my mother.</i>

15
00:00:31.031 --> 00:00:32.118
Hi. Shane.

16
00:00:32.119 --> 00:00:34.251
We need to talk.

17
00:00:41.302 --> 00:00:44.782
Let's talk about serial killers.

18
00:00:44.783 --> 00:00:47.568
Was the Bay Area Butcher
born a killer.

19
00:00:47.569 --> 00:00:50.701
or did his environment
turn him into one?

20
00:00:50.702 --> 00:00:56.055
Is a sociopath a result
of nature or nurture?

21
00:00:56.056 --> 00:00:59.971
Well. that is a question
that has plagued scientists

22
00:00:59.972 --> 00:01:02.235
and academics for centuries.

23
00:01:02.236 --> 00:01:05.368
In fact. some behavioral
psychiatrist at Quantico

24
00:01:05.369 --> 00:01:08.850
is probably asking that
very question right now.

25
00:01:08.851 --> 00:01:10.939
<i>Unfortunately.
they're looking for an answer</i>

26
00:01:10.940 --> 00:01:13.811
<i>they'll never find.</i>

27
00:01:13.812 --> 00:01:17.641
<i>I propose. while environment
clearly plays a part.</i>

28
00:01:17.642 --> 00:01:21.950
<i>it is the anatomical structure
of one's brain.</i>

29
00:01:21.951 --> 00:01:23.778
<i>our nature.</i>

30
00:01:23.779 --> 00:01:30.393
that will determine which of us
will become the next Butcher.

31
00:01:34.616 --> 00:01:36.443
Hey. man. you spare a few bucks?

32
00:01:36.444 --> 00:01:38.009
Just trying to get a hot meal.

33
00:01:38.010 --> 00:01:39.837
Tell you what.

34
00:01:39.838 --> 00:01:41.752
I'll do you one better.

35
00:01:41.753 --> 00:01:43.363
I'm looking for
paid participants

36
00:01:43.364 --> 00:01:44.886
for a research study.

37
00:01:44.887 --> 00:01:47.715
If you're interested.
I'll offer you a hot meal

38
00:01:47.716 --> 00:01:50.021
and $20 on top.

39
00:01:50.022 --> 00:01:51.936
What do you say?

40
00:01:51.937 --> 00:01:53.982
Huh?

41
00:02:06.213 --> 00:02:08.127
Cold night to be on
the streets. huh?

42
00:02:08.128 --> 00:02:10.172
Yeah. Uh...

43
00:02:10.173 --> 00:02:11.826
I'm working on getting a place.

44
00:02:11.827 --> 00:02:14.394
Saving up.

45
00:02:14.395 --> 00:02:18.528
I'm assuming your
family can't help?

46
00:02:18.529 --> 00:02:20.662
No. man. I kind of got no one.

47
00:02:21.837 --> 00:02:23.316
Mmm-mmm-mmm!

48
00:02:23.317 --> 00:02:26.449
My wife makes these. and
they're just... just delicious.

49
00:02:26.450 --> 00:02:28.625
Here. please help yourself.

50
00:02:28.626 --> 00:02:31.237
Unless you'd rather not
take candy from a stranger.

51
00:02:32.326 --> 00:02:34.154
No. I love toffee.
Thanks.

52
00:02:36.765 --> 00:02:38.069
So you're some kind
of teacher. huh?

53
00:02:38.070 --> 00:02:40.202
Uh. yes. neuroscience.

54
00:02:40.203 --> 00:02:42.900
I have an MD and PhD.

55
00:02:42.901 --> 00:02:45.033
which means I practice.

56
00:02:45.034 --> 00:02:47.035
and I do research.

57
00:02:47.036 --> 00:02:48.123
Oh. wow.

58
00:02:48.124 --> 00:02:49.603
I barely graduated daycare.

59
00:02:49.604 --> 00:02:51.257
Oh.

60
00:02:51.258 --> 00:02:54.042
Well. I'm sure you'll find
your purpose in this world.

61
00:02:54.043 --> 00:02:55.826
Um. yeah.

62
00:02:55.827 --> 00:02:58.046
school was never really...

63
00:03:00.789 --> 00:03:02.398
Never really...

64
00:03:13.976 --> 00:03:15.455
Well. good news. Johnny.

65
00:03:15.456 --> 00:03:17.893
Your life will not be in vain.

66
00:03:18.850 --> 00:03:21.548
I mean. I don't want
to sound condescending.

67
00:03:21.549 --> 00:03:25.466
but let's be honest.
you were going nowhere fast.

68
00:03:26.902 --> 00:03:27.902
What happened?

69
00:03:27.903 --> 00:03:29.077
Just relax.

70
00:03:29.078 --> 00:03:30.905
Almost there.

71
00:03:46.661 --> 00:03:47.965
No.

72
00:03:47.966 --> 00:03:49.924
No. no. no. no!

73
00:03:58.760 --> 00:04:00.717
There's really only so much
you can learn

74
00:04:00.718 --> 00:04:02.937
from textbooks and teachers.

75
00:04:02.938 --> 00:04:07.594
Real knowledge can only be
gained through experience

76
00:04:07.595 --> 00:04:11.989
and taking chances
that most people just

77
00:04:11.990 --> 00:04:14.905
don't have the stomach for.

78
00:04:14.906 --> 00:04:19.258
One of those chances might just
turn out to change the world.

79
00:04:19.259 --> 00:04:22.565
And who knows. Johnny.

80
00:04:22.566 --> 00:04:25.612
you might still
prove to be more important

81
00:04:25.613 --> 00:04:28.049
than you ever imagined.

82
00:04:43.326 --> 00:04:45.196
I'm sorry. I don't...
I don't know.

83
00:04:45.197 --> 00:04:49.157
This is... is a lot to take in.

84
00:04:49.158 --> 00:04:51.246
I understand.

85
00:04:51.247 --> 00:04:52.943
When did you realize?

86
00:04:52.944 --> 00:04:56.251
The moment I saw you
in the Command Center.

87
00:04:56.252 --> 00:04:58.471
So I pulled your
military DNA records

88
00:04:58.472 --> 00:05:00.777
and ran them against mine.

89
00:05:00.778 --> 00:05:02.605
When I was an inmate at the Pit.

90
00:05:02.606 --> 00:05:06.479
Dr. Dulles used to let me watch
some of your sessions with him.

91
00:05:06.480 --> 00:05:09.003
Those moments meant

92
00:05:09.004 --> 00:05:12.702
everything to me.

93
00:05:12.703 --> 00:05:15.488
Then once I was out
of the Pit...

94
00:05:15.489 --> 00:05:16.880
Graduated?

95
00:05:16.881 --> 00:05:20.536
That's what Dulles
liked to call it.

96
00:05:20.537 --> 00:05:22.364
And I finally had my freedom.

97
00:05:22.365 --> 00:05:26.194
he still refused to tell me
anything more about you

98
00:05:26.195 --> 00:05:27.456
or where you lived.

99
00:05:27.457 --> 00:05:30.067
And then...

100
00:05:30.068 --> 00:05:33.332
20 years later.

101
00:05:33.333 --> 00:05:36.335
here you are.

102
00:05:36.336 --> 00:05:38.424
I'm... I'm not

103
00:05:38.425 --> 00:05:41.209
really sure
what I'm supposed to say.

104
00:05:41.210 --> 00:05:44.125
You don't have to say anything.

105
00:05:44.126 --> 00:05:47.433
This can be whatever
you want it to be.

106
00:05:47.434 --> 00:05:49.173
Or don't.

107
00:05:49.174 --> 00:05:53.917
But I would very much like
to get to know you.

108
00:05:58.053 --> 00:06:00.054
You have my eyes.

109
00:06:11.849 --> 00:06:16.636
Uh-uh. half-caf with
cream and two sugars.

110
00:06:16.637 --> 00:06:18.551
Someone's paying attention.

111
00:06:18.552 --> 00:06:20.248
- Details matter.
- Hm.

112
00:06:20.249 --> 00:06:21.292
Oh. but did you...

113
00:06:21.293 --> 00:06:23.077
Pour the decaf in first?

114
00:06:23.078 --> 00:06:24.600
Yes.

115
00:06:24.601 --> 00:06:29.126
Although I haven't figured out
why you do that.

116
00:06:29.127 --> 00:06:32.260
And I plan on
remaining a mystery.

117
00:06:32.261 --> 00:06:34.044
Morales.

118
00:06:34.045 --> 00:06:35.394
What do we got?

119
00:06:35.395 --> 00:06:36.917
Facial rec picked up this photo.

120
00:06:36.918 --> 00:06:39.354
It was sent by a Harvard
undergrad to his roommates.

121
00:06:39.355 --> 00:06:41.574
I assume we already accessed
the phones remotely

122
00:06:41.575 --> 00:06:42.705
and scrubbed the image?

123
00:06:42.706 --> 00:06:44.620
- Done.
- Don't tell Congress.

124
00:06:44.621 --> 00:06:47.144
And the students have no idea
they just captured a real image

125
00:06:47.145 --> 00:06:48.624
of Sidney Fairfax.

126
00:06:48.625 --> 00:06:50.147
The Boston 9 case.

127
00:06:50.148 --> 00:06:52.149
Guess he was more than
a person of interest.

128
00:06:52.150 --> 00:06:54.369
Boston 9... why does that
sound so familiar?

129
00:06:54.370 --> 00:06:57.677
It's an infamous unsolved
case from 1990 to 1995.

130
00:06:57.678 --> 00:06:59.635
Nine bodies were found
buried in the remote woods

131
00:06:59.636 --> 00:07:01.158
beside the Concord River.

132
00:07:01.159 --> 00:07:04.466
each with a section
of their brain removed.

133
00:07:04.467 --> 00:07:06.294
It's never just a good old
shot to the chest anymore.

134
00:07:06.295 --> 00:07:07.556
is it?

135
00:07:07.557 --> 00:07:09.515
What?

136
00:07:09.516 --> 00:07:11.255
You know what I meant.

137
00:07:11.256 --> 00:07:14.520
You know. these cuts look
very professional.

138
00:07:14.521 --> 00:07:16.609
I mean. almost surgical.

139
00:07:16.610 --> 00:07:17.827
That's what
the cops thought. too.

140
00:07:17.828 --> 00:07:19.742
which is why Sidney Fairfax.

141
00:07:19.743 --> 00:07:21.962
an esteemed professor
wound up on their radar.

142
00:07:21.963 --> 00:07:23.442
along with
other rumored suspects.

143
00:07:23.443 --> 00:07:25.531
But before
they could build a case.

144
00:07:25.532 --> 00:07:28.925
he died in a one-car accident
driving home from Harvard.

145
00:07:28.926 --> 00:07:30.710
Big air quotes on that "one."

146
00:07:30.711 --> 00:07:32.407
Sounds to me like
somebody figured out

147
00:07:32.408 --> 00:07:34.278
Fairfax was the Boston 9 guy.

148
00:07:34.279 --> 00:07:35.802
didn't want the public
to know the truth.

149
00:07:35.803 --> 00:07:37.673
so they disappeared him
inside the Pit.

150
00:07:37.674 --> 00:07:38.892
Oh. you're right.
this is the first time

151
00:07:38.893 --> 00:07:40.154
the Pit has faked the death
of an inmate

152
00:07:40.155 --> 00:07:42.417
before they were caught
for their crimes.

153
00:07:42.418 --> 00:07:44.071
What do we have
on his therapies?

154
00:07:44.072 --> 00:07:46.465
From what I'm seeing. he
was never officially treated.

155
00:07:46.466 --> 00:07:48.989
There are no therapies.
no treatment logs. nothing.

156
00:07:48.990 --> 00:07:50.425
Whoever hid him in
the Pit really wanted

157
00:07:50.426 --> 00:07:51.731
to make sure he vanished.

158
00:07:51.732 --> 00:07:53.210
OK. Morales.
can you and the team pull up

159
00:07:53.211 --> 00:07:55.256
any public information...
biographies. interviews.

160
00:07:55.257 --> 00:07:56.562
anything that he's done?

161
00:07:56.563 --> 00:07:57.954
Anything we can use
to get inside his head.

162
00:07:57.955 --> 00:07:59.652
- We're on it.
- Hey.

163
00:07:59.653 --> 00:08:00.957
Sorry I'm late.

164
00:08:00.958 --> 00:08:03.046
You OK?

165
00:08:03.047 --> 00:08:04.308
Yeah. yeah.

166
00:08:04.309 --> 00:08:07.224
just set my alarm to p.m..
like an idiot.

167
00:08:07.225 --> 00:08:08.182
Where are we headed?

168
00:08:08.183 --> 00:08:09.357
Boston.

169
00:08:09.358 --> 00:08:11.446
Hope you brought a jacket.

170
00:08:27.376 --> 00:08:29.203
Hello. Professor.

171
00:08:43.392 --> 00:08:45.741
Professor Alanson?

172
00:08:52.096 --> 00:08:53.401
Hello?

173
00:09:07.242 --> 00:09:08.634
Campus.

174
00:09:08.635 --> 00:09:11.114
Hippo... hippopota... campus.

175
00:09:11.115 --> 00:09:16.729
Campumus is the
hippopamplemousse.

176
00:09:16.730 --> 00:09:18.165
Professor?

177
00:09:20.560 --> 00:09:21.690
A-Are you OK?

178
00:09:31.614 --> 00:09:34.355
Help me.

179
00:09:40.057 --> 00:09:41.449
Help!

180
00:09:41.450 --> 00:09:42.973
Somebody. help!

181
00:10:01.383 --> 00:10:04.733
All right.
Note the slightly reduced

182
00:10:04.734 --> 00:10:07.083
volume in the prefrontal lobe.

183
00:10:07.084 --> 00:10:09.085
the moderately
reduced connections

184
00:10:09.086 --> 00:10:12.828
between the amygdala
and the prefrontal cortex.

185
00:10:12.829 --> 00:10:15.439
Every serial killer
I have studied

186
00:10:15.440 --> 00:10:19.530
shares a number of these
anatomical features.

187
00:10:19.531 --> 00:10:22.316
Well. you may be wondering.
if we can just

188
00:10:22.317 --> 00:10:26.059
scan someone's brain and
determine their predisposition

189
00:10:26.060 --> 00:10:29.715
toward murderous violence.
shouldn't we be able to stop

190
00:10:29.716 --> 00:10:31.542
them before they start?

191
00:10:31.543 --> 00:10:34.763
Unfortunately. not so simple.

192
00:10:34.764 --> 00:10:37.592
because these unique structures

193
00:10:37.593 --> 00:10:41.378
are not isolated
to killers alone.

194
00:10:41.379 --> 00:10:43.163
For example.

195
00:10:43.164 --> 00:10:46.340
structurally.
this patient's brain

196
00:10:46.341 --> 00:10:49.735
is no different from your
average serial killer.

197
00:10:49.736 --> 00:10:52.651
Yet this scan belongs to...

198
00:10:52.652 --> 00:10:54.740
my assistant.
Mr. Clive Alanson.

199
00:10:56.220 --> 00:10:58.657
So far. he hasn't killed anyone

200
00:10:58.658 --> 00:11:00.354
that we know of.

201
00:11:02.444 --> 00:11:04.880
<i>So we have to ask.</i>

202
00:11:04.881 --> 00:11:06.577
<i>why is one a killer</i>

203
00:11:06.578 --> 00:11:08.710
<i>and the other my assistant?</i>

204
00:11:08.711 --> 00:11:12.932
<i>Where is that biological
switch inside their minds?</i>

205
00:11:12.933 --> 00:11:16.239
<i>And what flips it from off</i>

206
00:11:16.240 --> 00:11:18.894
<i>to on?</i>

207
00:11:18.895 --> 00:11:20.374
Loves the sound of
his own voice. doesn't he?

208
00:11:20.375 --> 00:11:21.767
Yeah. he does.

209
00:11:21.768 --> 00:11:23.856
Five years old Fairfax
was labeled a gifted child

210
00:11:23.857 --> 00:11:26.119
and wound up skipping
several grades.

211
00:11:26.120 --> 00:11:27.773
In multiple interviews.
he mentions feeling

212
00:11:27.774 --> 00:11:30.601
completely out of step
with his much older classmates.

213
00:11:30.602 --> 00:11:32.081
It's my guess that over time.

214
00:11:32.082 --> 00:11:33.779
Fairfax's antisocial traits

215
00:11:33.780 --> 00:11:35.781
bloomed into
a full-blown lifestyle.

216
00:11:35.782 --> 00:11:38.653
So he retreated into academia.
where his smarts were an asset.

217
00:11:38.654 --> 00:11:40.089
not a liability.
- Let me guess.

218
00:11:40.090 --> 00:11:42.352
He's one of those kids
that went to Harvard at 16.

219
00:11:42.353 --> 00:11:44.311
15.

220
00:11:44.312 --> 00:11:46.574
At 20.
he had his MD and his PhD.

221
00:11:46.575 --> 00:11:49.795
And at 25. he was a tenured
professor and a leading voice

222
00:11:49.796 --> 00:11:52.058
in the convergence
of criminal anatomy.

223
00:11:52.059 --> 00:11:54.408
neuroscience. and antisocial
personality disorder.

224
00:11:54.409 --> 00:11:56.976
Doogie Howser.
the serial killer.

225
00:11:56.977 --> 00:11:59.500
Now. that is a show
I would watch.

226
00:11:59.501 --> 00:12:03.112
Hey. what's the over-under on
serial killers being geniuses?

227
00:12:03.113 --> 00:12:05.462
On TV. yeah. pretty high.

228
00:12:05.463 --> 00:12:07.464
but not in real life.

229
00:12:07.465 --> 00:12:09.640
Sidney Fairfax was in
his own class of mind.

230
00:12:09.641 --> 00:12:11.120
like a Ted Kaczynski.
another Ivy Leaguer.

231
00:12:11.121 --> 00:12:12.861
or a Rodney Alcala.

232
00:12:12.862 --> 00:12:14.123
Alcala.

233
00:12:14.124 --> 00:12:15.559
The Dating Game Killer. UCLA.
- Mm-hmm.

234
00:12:15.560 --> 00:12:18.084
If these guys
are such brilliant geniuses.

235
00:12:18.085 --> 00:12:20.303
why are they making such
horrible life choices?

236
00:12:20.304 --> 00:12:22.915
'Cause he didn't see it
as a horrible life choice.

237
00:12:22.916 --> 00:12:25.134
Sidney savored the power
and control he felt

238
00:12:25.135 --> 00:12:26.832
over killing an innocent person.

239
00:12:26.833 --> 00:12:30.487
He could recognize his victim's
distress but didn't weight it.

240
00:12:30.488 --> 00:12:32.228
The consequences of
his actions on others

241
00:12:32.229 --> 00:12:33.969
meant absolutely nothing to him.

242
00:12:33.970 --> 00:12:35.666
Plus. being a professor
would have allowed him

243
00:12:35.667 --> 00:12:36.972
to hide in plain sight.

244
00:12:36.973 --> 00:12:38.582
I'm sure that was part
of the thrill.

245
00:12:38.583 --> 00:12:40.019
Yeah. super-thrilling stuff.

246
00:12:43.632 --> 00:12:45.111
Hey. Morales. what's up?

247
00:12:45.112 --> 00:12:47.548
<i>I've been monitoring
Boston PD scanners.</i>

248
00:12:47.549 --> 00:12:50.856
<i>Get this. Fairfax had an
assistant named Clive Alanson.</i>

249
00:12:50.857 --> 00:12:52.683
- Yeah. we know who he is.
<i>- Was.</i>

250
00:12:52.684 --> 00:12:55.469
<i>Alanson was just found dead
in his lab at Harvard.</i>

251
00:13:01.868 --> 00:13:02.911
Thank you.

252
00:13:02.912 --> 00:13:04.391
Thanks.

253
00:13:12.530 --> 00:13:14.009
Whoa.

254
00:13:14.010 --> 00:13:16.882
I did not take the professor
for a "Hellraiser" fan.

255
00:13:18.710 --> 00:13:21.234
If Morales can identify
what these pins are.

256
00:13:21.235 --> 00:13:24.063
maybe we can figure out
where Fairfax got them.

257
00:13:24.064 --> 00:13:25.629
What are we thinking? Torture?

258
00:13:25.630 --> 00:13:27.631
There's an injection site
on his carotid.

259
00:13:27.632 --> 00:13:29.372
Fairfax drugged him.

260
00:13:29.373 --> 00:13:32.071
If he wanted to torture him. he
would have left him wide awake.

261
00:13:32.072 --> 00:13:33.202
OK. so what are you thinking?

262
00:13:33.203 --> 00:13:35.335
Like. this was punishment. or?

263
00:13:35.336 --> 00:13:36.902
Whatever it was.
we need to figure out

264
00:13:36.903 --> 00:13:39.252
where this mad scientist
is going next.

265
00:13:39.253 --> 00:13:40.688
Morales. where are you
with facial rec.

266
00:13:40.689 --> 00:13:41.994
traffic cams. anything?

267
00:13:41.995 --> 00:13:43.909
<i>Still nothing.</i>

268
00:13:43.910 --> 00:13:45.736
What are you thinking. Bex?

269
00:13:47.696 --> 00:13:50.393
Let's find out if the kid who
found him is still on campus.

270
00:13:52.048 --> 00:13:53.919
They think I did it.

271
00:13:53.920 --> 00:13:55.094
They told me to get a lawyer.

272
00:13:55.095 --> 00:13:56.747
I... I don't have a lawyer.

273
00:13:56.748 --> 00:13:58.619
Hey. Jack. I need you
to do something for me. OK?

274
00:13:58.620 --> 00:14:00.577
Can you make two fists?

275
00:14:00.578 --> 00:14:01.840
Both hands?

276
00:14:01.841 --> 00:14:02.884
Tight.

277
00:14:02.885 --> 00:14:04.886
Squeeze really hard.

278
00:14:04.887 --> 00:14:06.583
Now release.

279
00:14:06.584 --> 00:14:08.324
You just went through
something really horrible.

280
00:14:08.325 --> 00:14:10.196
and right now. your brain
is flooding your body with...

281
00:14:10.197 --> 00:14:13.068
With epinephrine and cortisol.

282
00:14:13.069 --> 00:14:15.244
Yeah. by squeezing my fist.

283
00:14:15.245 --> 00:14:17.507
I am flushing the blood
to my muscles

284
00:14:17.508 --> 00:14:18.944
where chemicals can be absorbed.

285
00:14:18.945 --> 00:14:20.206
Yeah. yeah.

286
00:14:20.207 --> 00:14:22.643
Jack. we don't think
that you killed Alanson.

287
00:14:22.644 --> 00:14:24.775
Uh. can you get me out of here?

288
00:14:24.776 --> 00:14:27.953
We can. and we will.

289
00:14:27.954 --> 00:14:29.998
but we just need to ask you

290
00:14:29.999 --> 00:14:31.566
a few questions first.

291
00:14:36.005 --> 00:14:38.267
Can you tell us anything
about those pins?

292
00:14:38.268 --> 00:14:40.313
Our colleague identified
them as electrodes

293
00:14:40.314 --> 00:14:42.793
used in deep-brain stimulation.

294
00:14:42.794 --> 00:14:44.143
That's right.

295
00:14:44.144 --> 00:14:46.145
They're incredibly cutting edge.

296
00:14:46.146 --> 00:14:48.277
Whoever killed Alanson.
could they have

297
00:14:48.278 --> 00:14:50.149
gotten those pins in the lab?

298
00:14:50.150 --> 00:14:54.283
Yes. but I've never seen
DBS electrodes

299
00:14:54.284 --> 00:14:56.895
implanted in those areas
of the skull before.

300
00:14:56.896 --> 00:14:58.722
- Why not?
- 'Cause it's crazy.

301
00:14:58.723 --> 00:15:00.420
It's unsafe.

302
00:15:00.421 --> 00:15:03.292
It could cause strokes. hemorrhages.

303
00:15:03.293 --> 00:15:05.425
Do you know anyone who
would implant them like that?

304
00:15:05.426 --> 00:15:07.166
No. but I... I can tell you.
whoever did

305
00:15:07.167 --> 00:15:08.471
definitely knew
what they were doing.

306
00:15:08.472 --> 00:15:11.648
I mean. those were
freehand burr holes.

307
00:15:11.649 --> 00:15:13.215
I... I don't follow.

308
00:15:13.216 --> 00:15:16.044
Only a highly skilled
brain surgeon

309
00:15:16.045 --> 00:15:17.741
trained in the latest technology

310
00:15:17.742 --> 00:15:20.005
could have done that.

311
00:15:29.276 --> 00:15:31.233
<i>Hey. Shane. It's Sarah.</i>

312
00:15:31.234 --> 00:15:33.453
<i>I just wanted you to know
my dad passed away</i>

313
00:15:33.454 --> 00:15:35.498
<i>a few nights ago in his sleep.</i>

314
00:15:35.499 --> 00:15:38.153
<i>I'm just glad
he went peacefully.</i>

315
00:15:38.154 --> 00:15:41.026
<i>We can talk whenever.</i>

316
00:15:41.027 --> 00:15:42.810
Shane.

317
00:15:42.811 --> 00:15:45.204
Morales. I need you to pull up
Tom Beecher's medical file.

318
00:15:45.205 --> 00:15:46.422
Yeah.
Why not?

319
00:15:46.423 --> 00:15:48.337
Since we're on the topic
of barbaric

320
00:15:48.338 --> 00:15:50.209
experimental brain surgeries.

321
00:15:50.210 --> 00:15:52.820
How is it that a guy
who's in prison for 30 years

322
00:15:52.821 --> 00:15:54.822
performs a cutting-edge surgery
with technology

323
00:15:54.823 --> 00:15:57.520
that was developed decades
after he wound up in the Pit?

324
00:15:57.521 --> 00:15:59.392
You don't think Fairfax was
just sitting on the bench.

325
00:15:59.393 --> 00:16:02.003
No. I think
he was working down there.

326
00:16:02.004 --> 00:16:04.049
I mean. look. Tom Beecher.
he had brain surgeries

327
00:16:04.050 --> 00:16:05.267
performed in the Pit.

328
00:16:05.268 --> 00:16:06.834
We always assumed
that it was Dulles.

329
00:16:06.835 --> 00:16:09.619
But what if Fairfax was the one
actually performing them?

330
00:16:09.620 --> 00:16:11.708
I'm sending you
Beecher's records now.

331
00:16:11.709 --> 00:16:14.625
<i>Take a look at the letters
next to Dulles's signature.</i>

332
00:16:17.367 --> 00:16:19.238
SF. Sidney Fairfax.

333
00:16:19.239 --> 00:16:20.587
Seems like Dulles
wasn't the only one

334
00:16:20.588 --> 00:16:22.719
using Pit inmates as specimens.

335
00:16:22.720 --> 00:16:25.287
There are at least 20 other
patients with SF initials

336
00:16:25.288 --> 00:16:26.593
in their medical files.

337
00:16:26.594 --> 00:16:28.464
and that's just after
a 15-second search.

338
00:16:28.465 --> 00:16:31.076
Also explains why Fairfax's
Pit files never existed.

339
00:16:31.077 --> 00:16:33.078
He wasn't just an inmate.

340
00:16:33.079 --> 00:16:34.644
He was a visiting professor.

341
00:16:48.137 --> 00:16:49.746
Can I help you?

342
00:16:49.747 --> 00:16:50.921
Willa Sanchez?

343
00:16:50.922 --> 00:16:51.966
Yes.

344
00:16:51.967 --> 00:16:53.881
I'm with the University.

345
00:16:53.882 --> 00:16:56.319
My name is Dr. Fairfax.

346
00:17:01.411 --> 00:17:03.412
Dr. Charles.
we were hoping that you could

347
00:17:03.413 --> 00:17:04.979
help us with another inmate.

348
00:17:04.980 --> 00:17:07.721
<i>What can you tell us about
Professor Sidney Fairfax?</i>

349
00:17:07.722 --> 00:17:09.549
Was there any way that
he continued his work

350
00:17:09.550 --> 00:17:10.767
when he was in the Pit?

351
00:17:10.768 --> 00:17:15.208
Sidney's time in the Pit
was regrettable.

352
00:17:16.078 --> 00:17:18.906
<i>Yes. he continued his research.</i>

353
00:17:18.907 --> 00:17:22.214
<i>He was even encouraged to
by Dr. Dulles.</i>

354
00:17:22.215 --> 00:17:25.391
<i>Fairfax believed that serial
killers' brains shared</i>

355
00:17:25.392 --> 00:17:27.871
<i>specific anatomical traits.</i>

356
00:17:27.872 --> 00:17:29.873
<i>that biology could predict</i>

357
00:17:29.874 --> 00:17:32.920
<i>an individual's potential
for murder.</i>

358
00:17:32.921 --> 00:17:34.530
<i>So the population inside the Pit</i>

359
00:17:34.531 --> 00:17:39.274
<i>offered him access to hundreds
of ideal test subjects.</i>

360
00:17:41.886 --> 00:17:46.934
<i>Dr. Dulles was fascinated
by Sidney's work.</i>

361
00:17:46.935 --> 00:17:50.242
<i>despite the obvious
moral erosion.</i>

362
00:17:50.243 --> 00:17:51.460
OK.

363
00:17:51.461 --> 00:17:52.766
What can you tell us
about Fairfax's work

364
00:17:52.767 --> 00:17:54.333
in deep-brain stimulation?

365
00:17:54.334 --> 00:17:57.075
<i>Sidney believed
in select patients.</i>

366
00:17:57.076 --> 00:18:01.514
he could use DBS to stimulate
dormant. violent tendencies

367
00:18:01.515 --> 00:18:03.472
in nonviolent subjects.

368
00:18:03.473 --> 00:18:06.171
Like flipping a biological
switch in their minds.

369
00:18:06.172 --> 00:18:08.216
A noble pursuit
if the goal simply

370
00:18:08.217 --> 00:18:11.785
had been to flip the switch off
in violent offenders.

371
00:18:11.786 --> 00:18:13.265
Are you saying it wasn't?

372
00:18:13.266 --> 00:18:14.962
I'm saying
when it comes to the Pit.

373
00:18:14.963 --> 00:18:17.138
things are never as simple
as they seem.

374
00:18:17.139 --> 00:18:19.619
<i>If a switch can be turned off...</i>

375
00:18:19.620 --> 00:18:20.707
It can be turned on.

376
00:18:20.708 --> 00:18:22.100
<i>Exactly.</i>

377
00:18:22.101 --> 00:18:24.058
<i>Dulles believed
it was impossible.</i>

378
00:18:24.059 --> 00:18:25.929
<i>Of course inside the Pit.</i>

379
00:18:25.930 --> 00:18:27.627
<i>there weren't
any nonviolent offenders</i>

380
00:18:27.628 --> 00:18:29.281
<i>to test his theory upon.</i>

381
00:18:29.282 --> 00:18:32.588
<i>So he used other inmates
as disposable lab rats.</i>

382
00:18:34.069 --> 00:18:35.504
<i>OK. so who is right?</i>

383
00:18:35.505 --> 00:18:36.766
<i>We'll never know.</i>

384
00:18:36.767 --> 00:18:38.420
<i>Dulles lost his mind.</i>

385
00:18:38.421 --> 00:18:42.468
<i>And without Dulles. Fairfax
stayed locked in his cell.</i>

386
00:18:42.469 --> 00:18:44.252
<i>Until now.</i>

387
00:18:47.387 --> 00:18:48.909
Morales.

388
00:18:48.910 --> 00:18:51.694
I've got a report of a 911 call
about an injured woman

389
00:18:51.695 --> 00:18:53.261
wandering the streets
of Cambridge.

390
00:18:53.262 --> 00:18:55.829
She had.
"Things drilled into her head."

391
00:18:55.830 --> 00:18:57.831
ID says Willa Sanchez.

392
00:18:57.832 --> 00:18:59.224
Get this to the team

393
00:18:59.225 --> 00:19:01.661
and find out what hospital
they're taking her to.

394
00:19:04.055 --> 00:19:06.361
I'm going to have the doctor
come speak with you.

395
00:19:06.362 --> 00:19:09.016
OK. thank you.

396
00:19:09.017 --> 00:19:10.887
I have been on this
since the beginning.

397
00:19:10.888 --> 00:19:13.803
They're still working to
stabilize Willa Sanchez.

398
00:19:13.804 --> 00:19:17.242
But they said they
would let me know...

399
00:19:17.243 --> 00:19:18.853
Shane.

400
00:19:19.767 --> 00:19:22.203
Hey.

401
00:19:22.204 --> 00:19:23.465
Sorry.

402
00:19:23.466 --> 00:19:25.772
Uh. is Willa going to make it?

403
00:19:25.773 --> 00:19:27.643
Are you OK?

404
00:19:27.644 --> 00:19:30.907
You're just really
out of it today.

405
00:19:30.908 --> 00:19:32.126
Does this have
anything to do with

406
00:19:32.127 --> 00:19:33.868
why you were late this morning?

407
00:19:35.652 --> 00:19:37.000
Shane.

408
00:19:38.699 --> 00:19:40.700
Bureaucratic son of a bitch.

409
00:19:42.268 --> 00:19:43.529
That was Langley.

410
00:19:43.530 --> 00:19:45.052
Lazarus played me.

411
00:19:45.053 --> 00:19:48.925
Her whole balance of power
speech. garbage.

412
00:19:48.926 --> 00:19:50.188
What happened?

413
00:19:50.189 --> 00:19:52.190
She leveraged the attack
on Cyrus's convoy

414
00:19:52.191 --> 00:19:55.149
to assume military control over
all future prisoner transports.

415
00:19:55.150 --> 00:19:56.890
What?
She can do that?

416
00:19:56.891 --> 00:19:58.544
She just did.

417
00:19:58.545 --> 00:20:00.023
You can see her now.

418
00:20:00.024 --> 00:20:02.025
It's one visitor at a time.
and it has to be quick.

419
00:20:02.026 --> 00:20:03.549
The OR is already prepped.

420
00:20:17.738 --> 00:20:19.391
Willa.

421
00:20:25.311 --> 00:20:27.137
Willa. my name is
Rebecca Henderson.

422
00:20:27.138 --> 00:20:29.314
I'm here to help you.

423
00:20:29.315 --> 00:20:32.317
I want to catch the man
that did this to you.

424
00:20:34.842 --> 00:20:37.322
Ah. ah. ah.

425
00:20:37.323 --> 00:20:38.801
Ah. ah. ah!

426
00:20:38.802 --> 00:20:41.151
I'm... I'm late for class.

427
00:20:41.152 --> 00:20:42.936
No. You're in the hospital.

428
00:20:44.765 --> 00:20:46.113
Willa. can you hear me?

429
00:20:46.114 --> 00:20:48.246
No. no. no. no. I can't be late.

430
00:20:48.247 --> 00:20:49.551
I think we need
to end this here.

431
00:20:49.552 --> 00:20:51.292
No. no. no. no. no!
No. I can't be late.

432
00:20:52.555 --> 00:20:53.599
What are you going
to be late for. Willa?

433
00:20:53.600 --> 00:20:55.601
Doctor. he's at class.

434
00:20:55.602 --> 00:20:56.732
Always at class.

435
00:20:56.733 --> 00:20:58.821
Which class will
you be late for?

436
00:20:58.822 --> 00:21:02.042
N-n-n...

437
00:21:02.043 --> 00:21:03.478
neuro... neuro...
neuro... neuroscience.

438
00:21:03.479 --> 00:21:05.132
She's getting agitated.
That's enough.

439
00:21:05.133 --> 00:21:06.568
He locks the doors.
Can't be late.

440
00:21:06.569 --> 00:21:08.614
- Who? Who locks the doors?
- The professor.

441
00:21:08.615 --> 00:21:09.658
Professor Fairfax?

442
00:21:09.659 --> 00:21:10.790
Professor Dulles.

443
00:21:14.751 --> 00:21:16.491
So Willa Sanchez knew Dulles.

444
00:21:16.492 --> 00:21:17.797
Dulles knew Fairfax.

445
00:21:17.798 --> 00:21:20.147
Who knew Clive Alanson.

446
00:21:20.148 --> 00:21:22.932
Who had the brain of
a benign psychopath.

447
00:21:22.933 --> 00:21:24.325
You think Fairfax targeted Willa

448
00:21:24.326 --> 00:21:26.849
because she had the same
type of brain as Alanson?

449
00:21:26.850 --> 00:21:28.329
What if Fairfax was still trying

450
00:21:28.330 --> 00:21:29.722
to win his argument
with Dr. Dulles

451
00:21:29.723 --> 00:21:31.985
and use Dulles's former
students at MIT to do so?

452
00:21:31.986 --> 00:21:34.204
- Huh.
- Hey. Morales.

453
00:21:34.205 --> 00:21:35.641
<i>We need everything the Pit has
on Dr. Dulles.</i>

454
00:21:35.642 --> 00:21:37.251
Uh. I hate to say it.
but we've exhausted

455
00:21:37.252 --> 00:21:39.775
everything we have on Dulles.

456
00:21:39.776 --> 00:21:41.299
Except he does have a daughter

457
00:21:41.300 --> 00:21:42.822
<i>who lives in Boston.
Sarah Dulles.</i>

458
00:21:42.823 --> 00:21:43.823
- OK.
- All right.

459
00:21:43.824 --> 00:21:44.824
Send us her information.

460
00:21:44.825 --> 00:21:45.825
Maybe she knows something.

461
00:21:45.826 --> 00:21:47.306
<i>Yep. on it.</i>

462
00:21:49.090 --> 00:21:50.831
She doesn't.

463
00:21:52.311 --> 00:21:54.312
What?

464
00:21:54.313 --> 00:21:57.184
She just cleared out
her dad's place

465
00:21:57.185 --> 00:21:59.187
and sent me everything
that she had.

466
00:22:01.189 --> 00:22:03.408
<i>What the hell
are you talking about?</i>

467
00:22:03.409 --> 00:22:06.454
OK. it's a long story. and I
promise. I'm going to explain.

468
00:22:06.455 --> 00:22:09.631
But if Dulles has anything
on Fairfax in his files.

469
00:22:09.632 --> 00:22:11.024
it'll be at my apartment.

470
00:22:16.335 --> 00:22:18.248
Morales. I need you and Peck
to go to Shane's.

471
00:22:18.249 --> 00:22:20.425
<i>Get anything you can find.</i>

472
00:22:20.426 --> 00:22:22.427
<i>Comms off.</i>

473
00:22:22.428 --> 00:22:23.689
We gotta talk.

474
00:22:40.359 --> 00:22:41.707
Why?

475
00:22:41.708 --> 00:22:43.186
Why didn't you tell us
about Sarah?

476
00:22:43.187 --> 00:22:45.493
I know. I should have
told you earlier. but...

477
00:22:45.494 --> 00:22:46.929
But you thought
we wouldn't find out.

478
00:22:46.930 --> 00:22:48.061
No.

479
00:22:48.062 --> 00:22:49.062
No. it's not that at all.

480
00:22:49.063 --> 00:22:50.455
It's... it's complicated.

481
00:22:50.456 --> 00:22:52.587
Look. I told you.
I have been searching for

482
00:22:52.588 --> 00:22:54.502
my biological mother. right?

483
00:22:54.503 --> 00:22:57.592
And Dulles. he was my
best shot at finding her.

484
00:22:57.593 --> 00:22:59.638
Sarah sent me a message
about an hour ago.

485
00:22:59.639 --> 00:23:02.815
Dulles died a few days back.

486
00:23:02.816 --> 00:23:04.207
Days?

487
00:23:04.208 --> 00:23:06.209
You told us weeks ago
that he was already dead.

488
00:23:06.210 --> 00:23:08.777
Guys. I'm sorry that
I didn't tell you about this.

489
00:23:08.778 --> 00:23:10.736
but this was never about me
keeping secrets from you.

490
00:23:10.737 --> 00:23:12.433
This was about me
finding my mother.

491
00:23:15.916 --> 00:23:17.395
And I did.

492
00:23:19.702 --> 00:23:22.269
Actually. she found me.

493
00:23:27.057 --> 00:23:30.059
She's... Lazarus.

494
00:23:39.069 --> 00:23:40.505
You knew.

495
00:23:40.506 --> 00:23:41.985
For how long?

496
00:23:43.247 --> 00:23:45.510
A couple days.

497
00:23:45.511 --> 00:23:47.250
I was gonna tell you.

498
00:23:47.251 --> 00:23:48.556
But you didn't.

499
00:23:48.557 --> 00:23:51.080
What... you kept it from me.

500
00:23:51.081 --> 00:23:53.518
Yeah. we could say
the same thing about you.

501
00:23:53.519 --> 00:23:55.171
What?

502
00:23:55.172 --> 00:23:57.260
These aren't even close
to the same thing.

503
00:23:57.261 --> 00:23:59.567
No. I didn't have to tell you
about this.

504
00:23:59.568 --> 00:24:01.177
but I still did.

505
00:24:01.178 --> 00:24:04.833
Sure. months later. after
you intentionally lied to us.

506
00:24:04.834 --> 00:24:06.574
I have never withheld anything

507
00:24:06.575 --> 00:24:08.097
that could jeopardize a case.

508
00:24:08.098 --> 00:24:09.882
Never. never.

509
00:24:09.883 --> 00:24:11.971
This was strictly personal.

510
00:24:19.632 --> 00:24:20.981
You know what?

511
00:24:23.418 --> 00:24:24.592
If he...

512
00:24:24.593 --> 00:24:26.073
No. no.
Stop. stop. stop.

513
00:24:27.944 --> 00:24:30.250
What. am I supposed
to go after him?

514
00:24:30.251 --> 00:24:32.600
Fairfax is out there.

515
00:24:32.601 --> 00:24:33.993
Let's focus on that.

516
00:24:36.126 --> 00:24:40.129
Of all the gin joints in all
the towns in all the world.

517
00:24:40.130 --> 00:24:42.785
Dulles's files were in
Shane's apartment all along.

518
00:24:44.265 --> 00:24:45.308
Yeah.

519
00:24:45.309 --> 00:24:47.267
You don't seem surprised.

520
00:24:47.268 --> 00:24:49.095
I'm learning not to be
shocked by anything

521
00:24:49.096 --> 00:24:51.140
when it comes to this job.
or anyone.

522
00:24:51.141 --> 00:24:52.185
No.

523
00:24:53.274 --> 00:24:54.796
No. Shane is solid.

524
00:24:54.797 --> 00:24:58.365
Whatever this is.
he had a good reason.

525
00:25:01.325 --> 00:25:03.022
Um...

526
00:25:03.023 --> 00:25:04.763
Wait.

527
00:25:04.764 --> 00:25:07.635
Look at this.
It's...

528
00:25:07.636 --> 00:25:10.159
Willa Sanchez.

529
00:25:10.160 --> 00:25:13.989
This is from a 2002
longitudinal study

530
00:25:13.990 --> 00:25:17.906
when Dulles was
still chair at MIT.

531
00:25:17.907 --> 00:25:21.780
The cohort is 30
freshmen students.

532
00:25:21.781 --> 00:25:25.174
"Subject shows signs of
reduced frontal lobe volume.

533
00:25:25.175 --> 00:25:27.786
"reduced connections between
the prefrontal cortex

534
00:25:27.787 --> 00:25:29.483
and the amygdala."

535
00:25:29.484 --> 00:25:30.963
That's the way Fairfax described

536
00:25:30.964 --> 00:25:33.443
the Bay Area Butcher's brain
at his lecture.

537
00:25:33.444 --> 00:25:37.535
If everyone from this study
has the same description...

538
00:25:39.712 --> 00:25:42.627
Dulles must have shared it
with Fairfax at the Pit.

539
00:25:45.108 --> 00:25:48.720
Any one of these people
could be Fairfax's next victim.

540
00:26:28.978 --> 00:26:30.413
Got it.
Yes. ma'am.

541
00:26:30.414 --> 00:26:31.806
I'll let the team know.

542
00:26:31.807 --> 00:26:34.026
<i>Guys. I've got locations
on all 30 individuals</i>

543
00:26:34.027 --> 00:26:35.680
<i>who participated in the study.</i>

544
00:26:35.681 --> 00:26:37.595
Only three
are still in the area.

545
00:26:37.596 --> 00:26:39.684
Sending you their addresses now.

546
00:26:41.512 --> 00:26:43.339
None of these are far.

547
00:26:43.340 --> 00:26:44.471
We're on it.

548
00:27:08.670 --> 00:27:10.105
<i>You've reached Sarah Dulles.</i>

549
00:27:10.106 --> 00:27:11.716
<i>I can't come
to the phone right now.</i>

550
00:27:11.717 --> 00:27:13.587
<i>Please leave a message.</i>

551
00:27:13.588 --> 00:27:15.633
Hey. Sarah.

552
00:27:15.634 --> 00:27:17.286
It's. uh...

553
00:27:17.287 --> 00:27:19.288
well. it's Shane.

554
00:27:19.289 --> 00:27:21.682
I'm actually in Boston.

555
00:27:21.683 --> 00:27:24.032
and. uh. well.
I... I learned some things.

556
00:27:24.033 --> 00:27:26.818
and I was hoping we could talk.

557
00:27:26.819 --> 00:27:31.257
So. uh. I... I looked at
your dad's place. but...

558
00:27:33.913 --> 00:27:35.783
you're not home.

559
00:28:17.783 --> 00:28:18.826
Sir?

560
00:28:18.827 --> 00:28:20.349
Sir. I'm with the police.

561
00:28:26.182 --> 00:28:28.054
Oh. damn.

562
00:28:31.753 --> 00:28:35.800
Buddy.

563
00:28:35.801 --> 00:28:37.671
We need to get you
some help. all right?

564
00:28:37.672 --> 00:28:41.457
But first. I need to know.
where is Professor Fairfax?

565
00:28:45.288 --> 00:28:46.985
OK.

566
00:28:46.986 --> 00:28:49.030
Ahh!

567
00:28:54.733 --> 00:28:55.950
It's Shane.

568
00:28:55.951 --> 00:28:57.822
Hey.

569
00:28:57.823 --> 00:28:59.868
421 Pine Street now.

570
00:29:02.741 --> 00:29:04.959
I'm going to need you
to put the plates down.

571
00:29:04.960 --> 00:29:06.221
Listen.
Listen. buddy.

572
00:29:06.222 --> 00:29:07.440
I do not want to hurt you.

573
00:29:07.441 --> 00:29:09.442
Help is on the way.

574
00:29:09.443 --> 00:29:11.836
I need you to stay
where you are. OK?

575
00:29:13.534 --> 00:29:15.840
- No!
- Ahh!

576
00:29:15.841 --> 00:29:17.972
Just relax. OK?

577
00:29:17.973 --> 00:29:19.060
I'm here to help you.

578
00:29:20.062 --> 00:29:21.323
Whoa. whoa! Hey!

579
00:29:22.978 --> 00:29:24.370
Sorry.

580
00:29:30.029 --> 00:29:31.681
OK. All right.

581
00:29:31.682 --> 00:29:33.205
Ah!

582
00:29:53.313 --> 00:29:54.835
Mm.

583
00:29:54.836 --> 00:29:57.620
There again. reduced activity
in the amygdala.

584
00:29:57.621 --> 00:30:00.362
But the orbitofrontal cortex
is higher than average.

585
00:30:00.363 --> 00:30:02.364
For his age group. yes.

586
00:30:02.365 --> 00:30:04.236
but he is already showing signs

587
00:30:04.237 --> 00:30:07.109
of an overly active
ventral striatum.

588
00:30:07.980 --> 00:30:11.243
We'll see what happens
once he hits puberty.

589
00:30:13.246 --> 00:30:15.377
<i>Shane. keep going.</i>

590
00:30:15.378 --> 00:30:16.639
OK.

591
00:30:16.640 --> 00:30:19.207
I just want to do better
than last time.

592
00:30:19.208 --> 00:30:22.036
<i>If I do better. can I go home?</i>

593
00:30:22.037 --> 00:30:25.257
<i>You can go home when we're done.</i>

594
00:30:44.886 --> 00:30:46.756
Oh. you're awake.

595
00:30:46.757 --> 00:30:47.933
Splendid.

596
00:30:49.804 --> 00:30:52.066
I cannot tell you
how often I have thought

597
00:30:52.067 --> 00:30:53.502
about you over the years.

598
00:30:53.503 --> 00:30:56.810
The little boy born in the Pit.

599
00:30:56.811 --> 00:31:00.466
There was always something
so special about you.

600
00:31:00.467 --> 00:31:02.990
You remember me?

601
00:31:02.991 --> 00:31:04.035
Huh?

602
00:31:04.036 --> 00:31:05.340
No. no. no.

603
00:31:05.341 --> 00:31:06.994
It's OK if you don't.

604
00:31:06.995 --> 00:31:11.956
But I think that you and I are
haunted by the same question...

605
00:31:11.957 --> 00:31:14.698
nurture or nature?

606
00:31:18.572 --> 00:31:21.487
<i>Guys. that address
is Dulles's townhouse.</i>

607
00:31:21.488 --> 00:31:22.967
Right.
Go right.

608
00:31:22.968 --> 00:31:24.490
Yeah. I'm familiar
with which way right is.

609
00:31:28.974 --> 00:31:31.410
Dulles wanted you
to have a happy childhood

610
00:31:31.411 --> 00:31:33.499
to prove that environment shapes

611
00:31:33.500 --> 00:31:35.849
the mind more than biology.

612
00:31:35.850 --> 00:31:39.766
He wanted so desperately for
you just to be a normal kid.

613
00:31:39.767 --> 00:31:45.119
But somewhere inside him.
he knew you couldn't be.

614
00:31:45.120 --> 00:31:48.775
And I think that you.
my perfect test subject.

615
00:31:48.776 --> 00:31:51.386
have been brought back to me

616
00:31:51.387 --> 00:31:54.868
like some act
of divine providence

617
00:31:54.869 --> 00:31:58.350
to finally prove
that I am right.

618
00:32:07.490 --> 00:32:11.580
Psychopathy on demand
is possible.

619
00:32:11.581 --> 00:32:13.669
If only Dulles
were here to see this.

620
00:32:14.889 --> 00:32:18.413
What... oh. you have
something to add?

621
00:32:18.414 --> 00:32:19.893
You don't know
what you're talking about.

622
00:32:19.894 --> 00:32:22.026
You want to see
a killer's brain?

623
00:32:22.027 --> 00:32:22.983
Hmm?

624
00:32:22.984 --> 00:32:24.593
Why don't we open up your head?

625
00:32:24.594 --> 00:32:27.031
I'll bet you've taken more
lives than I have. my friend.

626
00:32:27.032 --> 00:32:29.685
Not... in the line of duty
and self-defense.

627
00:32:29.686 --> 00:32:30.991
It was protecting people.

628
00:32:30.992 --> 00:32:32.732
It's not...
it's not the same thing.

629
00:32:32.733 --> 00:32:35.213
I know you believe that.
but when we're done here.

630
00:32:35.214 --> 00:32:37.824
you will understand
the truth about yourself.

631
00:32:37.825 --> 00:32:40.348
You will understand
what it means

632
00:32:40.349 --> 00:32:42.263
to be the son of Evelyn Lazarus.

633
00:32:42.264 --> 00:32:43.917
Or do you call her Caitlin?

634
00:32:43.918 --> 00:32:45.832
You know nothing
about her anymore.

635
00:32:45.833 --> 00:32:49.227
I helped make Evelyn
Lazarus what she is today.

636
00:32:49.228 --> 00:32:50.968
I think I know a thing or two.

637
00:32:50.969 --> 00:32:53.057
Your mother was just
the beginning. Shane.

638
00:32:53.058 --> 00:32:56.756
But you. I think.
may be the end.

639
00:32:56.757 --> 00:32:59.541
I have waited 30 years
to get inside

640
00:32:59.542 --> 00:33:01.065
that little head of yours.

641
00:33:01.066 --> 00:33:02.283
Yeah. you can drill
all the holes you want.

642
00:33:02.284 --> 00:33:05.417
but the only psychopath
down here is you.

643
00:33:08.073 --> 00:33:09.421
Let's find out.

644
00:33:14.253 --> 00:33:15.993
That's a good boy.

645
00:33:24.872 --> 00:33:26.046
Sir.

646
00:33:30.356 --> 00:33:31.399
He's alive.

647
00:33:31.400 --> 00:33:33.271
Sir. can you hear me?

648
00:33:34.664 --> 00:33:36.317
Don't worry.
this is just a mild sedative.

649
00:33:36.318 --> 00:33:37.884
It won't knock you out.

650
00:33:37.885 --> 00:33:40.452
but it will keep you
from moving around too much

651
00:33:40.453 --> 00:33:42.845
once I start to cut.

652
00:33:42.846 --> 00:33:45.761
You'll be pleased to know
that brain tissue

653
00:33:45.762 --> 00:33:48.938
has no pain receptors.

654
00:33:48.939 --> 00:33:51.767
Unfortunately.
the scalp most certainly does.

655
00:33:51.768 --> 00:33:53.987
So if you can handle
the drill...

656
00:33:53.988 --> 00:33:55.815
We're gold.

657
00:33:55.816 --> 00:33:58.252
So let's just
give that a moment.

658
00:33:58.253 --> 00:34:00.428
and then we can begin.

659
00:34:07.349 --> 00:34:10.743
Shane. you're doing great.

660
00:34:22.669 --> 00:34:24.800
Don't scream.

661
00:34:24.801 --> 00:34:27.629
They don't like it
when we scream.

662
00:34:30.329 --> 00:34:31.590
<i>911. what's your emergency?</i>

663
00:34:31.591 --> 00:34:33.592
We need an ambulance
at 421 Pine.

664
00:34:36.248 --> 00:34:37.771
Where the hell is Shane?

665
00:34:41.818 --> 00:34:43.776
Shane can't have just
disappeared into thin air.

666
00:34:43.777 --> 00:34:45.778
What are we missing?

667
00:34:45.779 --> 00:34:46.779
We need to talk to someone

668
00:34:46.780 --> 00:34:48.824
that knew Fairfax and Dulles.

669
00:34:50.175 --> 00:34:51.523
Agent Henderson?

670
00:34:51.524 --> 00:34:53.394
<i>Shane was taken
by Sidney Fairfax.</i>

671
00:34:53.395 --> 00:34:55.483
Look. I know you care about him
as much as I do.

672
00:34:55.484 --> 00:34:57.224
How can I help?

673
00:34:57.225 --> 00:35:00.401
We tracked Fairfax to a
townhouse owned by Dr. Dulles.

674
00:35:00.402 --> 00:35:02.969
There is no sign that
Shane or Fairfax are here.

675
00:35:02.970 --> 00:35:04.971
You're in the right place.
just not the right level.

676
00:35:04.972 --> 00:35:06.103
We searched the whole house.

677
00:35:06.104 --> 00:35:09.193
No. you haven't.

678
00:35:20.205 --> 00:35:22.206
Of course.
there's a creepy doorway.

679
00:35:35.872 --> 00:35:37.743
Fairfax. freeze!

680
00:35:37.744 --> 00:35:40.354
Make one more move. and I
will shoot you where you stand.

681
00:35:40.355 --> 00:35:42.095
Well. that would be
a terrible miscalculation.

682
00:35:42.096 --> 00:35:43.705
because I've got a cranial drill

683
00:35:43.706 --> 00:35:46.055
4 millimeters from plunging
into little Shane's

684
00:35:46.056 --> 00:35:47.753
temporal lobe.

685
00:35:47.754 --> 00:35:48.884
I don't know. Doc.

686
00:35:48.885 --> 00:35:50.234
I'm a pretty good shot.

687
00:35:50.235 --> 00:35:52.584
Well. you're welcome
to take your chances. OK?

688
00:35:52.585 --> 00:35:56.501
But I'm telling you that
one flick of my finger.

689
00:35:56.502 --> 00:35:58.242
and it's the end
for your friend here.

690
00:35:58.243 --> 00:35:59.809
Wait. stop!

691
00:36:01.071 --> 00:36:02.942
Shane is not your lab rat.

692
00:36:02.943 --> 00:36:05.249
He is brave and selfless.

693
00:36:05.250 --> 00:36:07.164
He is a decorated marine.

694
00:36:07.165 --> 00:36:10.210
and yet he is way too humble
to actually talk about that.

695
00:36:10.211 --> 00:36:12.734
Uh-huh. he also has the brain
of a killer.

696
00:36:12.735 --> 00:36:14.040
So...

697
00:36:14.041 --> 00:36:16.085
It doesn't matter
how many holes you drill.

698
00:36:16.086 --> 00:36:18.740
you won't change who Shane is.

699
00:36:18.741 --> 00:36:22.614
who he has chosen to be.

700
00:36:22.615 --> 00:36:24.355
He cares more deeply
about people

701
00:36:24.356 --> 00:36:26.922
than anyone I have ever met.

702
00:36:26.923 --> 00:36:30.099
He is kind. he's loyal.

703
00:36:30.100 --> 00:36:31.231
and he can quite literally

704
00:36:31.232 --> 00:36:33.233
fall asleep wherever.

705
00:36:33.234 --> 00:36:34.843
What do you possibly hope
to gain

706
00:36:34.844 --> 00:36:38.891
with these stupid
sentimental arguments?

707
00:36:38.892 --> 00:36:40.197
Time.

708
00:36:42.112 --> 00:36:43.983
Ahh!

709
00:36:49.990 --> 00:36:51.251
He's down.

710
00:36:52.949 --> 00:36:54.776
It took you guys long enough.

711
00:36:54.777 --> 00:36:56.735
Yeah. we were pretty pissed.

712
00:36:56.736 --> 00:36:59.303
You know. you didn't need
to get abducted

713
00:36:59.304 --> 00:37:02.131
to remind us how much
we care about you.

714
00:37:02.132 --> 00:37:05.657
Worked. didn't it?

715
00:37:16.234 --> 00:37:18.147
All right.
the team just cleaned up

716
00:37:18.148 --> 00:37:19.888
everything at Dulles's place.

717
00:37:19.889 --> 00:37:23.240
And Fairfax's body
is en route back to Cheyenne.

718
00:37:23.241 --> 00:37:25.286
What a day.

719
00:37:29.334 --> 00:37:31.727
So listen. I want to...

720
00:37:33.338 --> 00:37:34.599
I want to say something
to you guys.

721
00:37:34.600 --> 00:37:36.165
Listen. you're good. man.

722
00:37:36.166 --> 00:37:37.341
We're sorry.

723
00:37:37.342 --> 00:37:38.298
You don't need to say anything.

724
00:37:38.299 --> 00:37:39.560
No. I...

725
00:37:39.561 --> 00:37:41.127
I do.

726
00:37:44.436 --> 00:37:47.873
So I've had this secret

727
00:37:47.874 --> 00:37:50.397
from the time I was 15.

728
00:37:50.398 --> 00:37:52.486
That's when I found out

729
00:37:52.487 --> 00:37:55.097
my biological mother
was a murderer.

730
00:37:55.098 --> 00:37:58.144
Since then. I've been keeping
that secret. you know?

731
00:37:58.145 --> 00:38:01.365
And I've spent so long
just guarding it

732
00:38:01.366 --> 00:38:04.542
and keeping people at arm's
length because of it

733
00:38:04.543 --> 00:38:06.065
that I...

734
00:38:08.198 --> 00:38:10.852
I've never known
how to put it down.

735
00:38:13.987 --> 00:38:16.380
But now.

736
00:38:16.381 --> 00:38:19.208
for the first time. maybe ever.
with you two.

737
00:38:19.209 --> 00:38:21.863
I have something to lose.

738
00:38:24.214 --> 00:38:26.955
So I'm sorry.

739
00:38:26.956 --> 00:38:28.305
I'm sorry.

740
00:38:34.747 --> 00:38:38.097
To putting it all
out in the open.

741
00:38:38.098 --> 00:38:41.056
I will drink to that.

742
00:38:55.071 --> 00:38:56.550
Got your message.

743
00:38:56.551 --> 00:38:58.378
Please. come sit.

744
00:39:01.295 --> 00:39:04.471
I wanted to thank you

745
00:39:04.472 --> 00:39:06.995
for saving Shane's life

746
00:39:06.996 --> 00:39:10.434
and for ridding the world
of Dr. Sidney Fairfax.

747
00:39:10.435 --> 00:39:12.436
Um. yeah.

748
00:39:12.437 --> 00:39:13.915
OK. I'm not really sure
what this is.

749
00:39:13.916 --> 00:39:16.962
but you should know that
Shane has told us everything.

750
00:39:16.963 --> 00:39:19.878
Not everything.

751
00:39:19.879 --> 00:39:22.489
There are still some pieces
I haven't shared with him.

752
00:39:22.490 --> 00:39:24.970
So what. you're gonna
share them with me now?

753
00:39:24.971 --> 00:39:27.276
There's no excuse
for what I did.

754
00:39:27.277 --> 00:39:29.583
but there is context.

755
00:39:29.584 --> 00:39:32.673
Were you ever bullied
in school. Rebecca?

756
00:39:32.674 --> 00:39:34.240
Bullies aren't just in school.

757
00:39:34.241 --> 00:39:37.156
Indeed. but mine were.

758
00:39:37.157 --> 00:39:38.767
And they were merciless.

759
00:39:40.247 --> 00:39:44.511
I was 17 years old.
not comfortable in my own skin.

760
00:39:44.512 --> 00:39:48.342
and I was not equipped to
navigate what was done to me.

761
00:39:49.474 --> 00:39:51.562
I didn't care
about the consequences.

762
00:39:51.563 --> 00:39:53.302
All I cared about was

763
00:39:53.303 --> 00:39:57.611
if I became the killer.

764
00:39:57.612 --> 00:40:02.050
I'd no longer be the victim.

765
00:40:03.531 --> 00:40:05.837
What I didn't know was that
there was something

766
00:40:05.838 --> 00:40:08.883
wrong with me.

767
00:40:08.884 --> 00:40:12.496
what I would later
come to understand

768
00:40:12.497 --> 00:40:15.890
as homicidal psychopathy.

769
00:40:15.891 --> 00:40:19.112
But Dr. Dulles
and the Pit cured me.

770
00:40:19.895 --> 00:40:24.203
I served my time.
and now I serve my country.

771
00:40:32.821 --> 00:40:35.736
It's a very sympathetic story.

772
00:40:35.737 --> 00:40:39.871
Reform is possible. Rebecca.

773
00:40:42.265 --> 00:40:45.485
And I'm living proof.

774
00:40:52.014 --> 00:40:53.014
She's here.

775
00:40:54.626 --> 00:40:59.020
Hey. um.
how'd it go with Lazarus?

776
00:40:59.021 --> 00:41:01.196
I think she's one of
the most dangerous sociopaths

777
00:41:01.197 --> 00:41:02.546
I've ever met.

778
00:41:02.547 --> 00:41:04.591
And whatever she's up to.

